  "texts": [
    "An interesting exception is the work in Li et al. (2023a, b), which uses several health data types (diagnosis, medication, procedure, examinations, blood pressure, drinking status, smoking status, and body mass index).",
    "However, such data are part of the same vocabulary, and thus, the learning process cannot explore the particular semantics of each.",
    "In other words, the model does not know if a token represents, for example, a medication or a diagnosis.",
    "A different approach explicitly indicates this type, such as in Prakash et al. (2021).",
    "This additional semantics can buster the efficiency and effectiveness of the learning process, similar to natural language processing, when the model knows that a token represents a noun or an adjective."
  ],
